latestPosts.caption:
Two hands.
One plate.
A thousand sprinkles whispering secrets in Esperanto.

The cone is not a cone.
It is a portal.
To childhood. To betrayal. To that time you cried at a county fair because your cousin won the cakewalk.

Who do these hands belong to?
Are they lovers? Enemies?
Two fragments of the same dream, colliding over dairy-based desire?

This is not dessert.
This is destiny.
Melting slowly under the weight of your unresolved memories.

#JuniorCones #SurrealSnacks #DalíLickedThisFirst #DreamsTasteLikeSprinkles

latestPosts.caption:
the cone is small.
but so were we, once.
running barefoot through summer. no bills. no heartbreak. just drips down our wrists and the sun in our eyes.
now i’m here—grown, tired, overthinking—holding this tiny cone like it’s a time machine.
and for 30 seconds… it is.
thank you, costco. thank you, junior cone.

#juniorcones #memorycone #costcospirituality #icecreamrealizations #brothersicecream

You’ve been warned. 😋🍦✨ Junior Cones @brothersicecream 😍🍦 SoCal-based family brand that’s been making premium frozen desserts since the ’70s—and I love supporting local companies that actually deliver on flavor., these mini cones are the real deal:
✅ Real vanilla ice cream
✅ Quality chocolate coating
✅ Naturally-colored rainbow sprinkles
✅ Just 110 calories per cone
They’re nostalgic, crunchy, creamy, and the perfect guilt-free treat for a hot summer night (or two… or five).
🫶 Did you know ice cream cones date back to 1904? They made their big debut at the St. Louis World’s Fair—and now, 120 years later, they’ve officially reached peak snack form with these!!
